{"id":28214,"title":"Edgar Allan Poe and neurology.","abstract":"Edgar Allan Poe was one of the most celebrated writers of all time. He published several masterpieces, some of which include references to neurological diseases. Poe suffered from recurrent depression, suggesting a bipolar disorder, as well as alcohol and drug abuse, which in fact led to his death from complications related to alcoholism. Various hypotheses were put forward, including Wernicke's encephalopathy. ","date":"2014-06-26","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24964115","annotations":[{"name":"Bipolar disorder","weight":0.865191,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bipolar_disorder"},{"name":"Alcoholism","weight":0.800515,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcoholism"},{"name":"Neurology","weight":0.793943,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neurology"},{"name":"Substance abuse","weight":0.734616,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Substance_abuse"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.728515,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Neurological disorder","weight":0.726596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neurological_disorder"},{"name":"Major depressive disorder","weight":0.723286,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Major_depressive_disorder"},{"name":"Alcohol","weight":0.70749,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.701843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Death","weight":0.672208,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death"},{"name":"Edgar Allan Poe","weight":0.528889,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edgar_Allan_Poe"},{"name":"Encephalopathy","weight":0.520792,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Encephalopathy"},{"name":"Hypothesis","weight":0.519298,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyp